OLOR=#000033>12:00:23 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Just a thought....</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">This isn't neccessarily a Shitlist on someone...this is more a less a piece of advice from personal experience.<br>
<br>
A few weeks ago in Timorous Deep I was camping spirocs. I noticed a mid 30's Necro attempting to Camp Oowamp (sp?). She must have died from a slight mishap and then zoned back into Timorous Deep to resume her camp. A druid (not saying a name because of how this turned out...you'll see) was in her spot killing the ogre. Well shouts and ooc's ensued about how she was there first and just because she died did not mean she gave up her camp. The druid replied how it wasn't his problem if she died. After a few minutes I decided to check out the problem because it continued for so long. I walked up and talked to both of them. Seeing as in my opinion dieing doesn't mean you have given up the camp (it doesn't help that you can't bind in TD cuz that means you have to zone and give time to others to take your camp when usually you just bind in the zone so that technically you never left) I told her to group with me and out nuke him to show him a thing or two about KSing. Of course on the next pop we sent pets in and used only necro nukes (not the best but together we outdamaged him). NOW I KNOW THAT WAS WRONG of me to intentionally KS him. But then I reverted to tells to him directly. I told him to think back to when he was her level and how all of us no matter what has been KSed or camps stolen from us all before. I asked him what he was there for. Batskull earrings (int items for a wis caster). I told him well for her it's an xp camp not just an item camp which technically gave her rights to it. I'm not a rules lawyer but I know gms will defend someone getting xp and not someone camping items. He said he was getting xp from it (which I learned later was a lie since he was higher level than me by about 2 levels and I tried camping him for a bit and never got any xp). So I told him bluntly &quot;I doubt she will be here forever and that I doubt even more she could hold it for that long to begin with.&quot; I asked him politely to leave for just a little while and she would be gone soon enough. I even gave him one of my Batskull earrings. He said he couldn't take it for free and gave me a sheer bone mask (not worth as much but if he didn't want it for free and it bought the necro more time to attempt a camp then fine) Me and the druid actually chatted for a while and he appologized to the necro. <br>
<br>
My point in all of this is if situations are handled maturely and with the knowledge that THIS IS JUST A GAME I think half the time none of these posts would be made. Yes there are some real D*ck Heads out there that will be @$$'s just because they can, but for the most part I find it's just people in a bad mood and that if you talk to them like they are people and not just a bunch of pixels they will relent and everyone will be happy in the end.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
